---
import ChapterLayout from "../layouts/ChapterLayout.astro";
import BookCard from "../components/BookCard.astro";
import Divider from "../components/Divider.astro";
---

<ChapterLayout title="Novels" chapter="Chapter II">
  <p class="drop-cap text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    Stories have always been my way of making sense of the world. Each novel is a door into a place I've spent years imagining — full of characters who feel like old friends and conflicts that keep me awake at night. Here are the worlds I've built so far.
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-8">
    <BookCard
      title="The First Chronicle"
      synopsis="In a kingdom where memory is currency and forgetting is a crime, a young archivist discovers a gap in the royal ledger that could unravel everything. A sweeping fantasy of power, identity, and the stories we tell ourselves to survive."
      amazonUrl="#"
    />

    <Divider />

    <BookCard
      title="Ember and Ash"
      synopsis="Two rival fire-keepers must join forces when an ancient darkness threatens to extinguish the last flame in their dying world. A tale of trust, sacrifice, and the spark that refuses to go out."
      amazonUrl="#"
    />
  </div>

  <Divider class="mt-10" />

  <p class="text-center text-charcoal/50 font-heading italic text-sm mt-4">
    More stories are on their way. The ink is still wet.
  </p>
</ChapterLayout>
